It feels very brittle that the scene tabs will set a property of EditorNode and then the editor acts based on that property, and it has to be manually cleared. It's rather bug-prone.

Are there cases when `tab_context_idx` is needed after the menu callback? You could add a method to EditorSceneTabs that return the tab for which the option should be applied, but then it would be cleaner if it was used only for menu options from scene tabs (which means the scene tabs would have to get its own option id for scene save etc.), but without duplicating too much the code.

So for example the code for closing scene could look like
```C++
case SCENE_CLOSE: {
	_scene_tab_closed(editor_data.get_edited_scene());
} break;
case EditorSceneTabs::SCENE_CLOSE {
	int scene_to_close = scene_tabs->get_option_tab();
	_scene_tab_closed(scene_to_close);
} break;
```

